    <h3 class="name text-center">1. Temple University - Philadelphia, PA</h3>
    <p class="description">Price, customizability, and quality are the three pillars of Temple University’s Fox School
      of Business, which happens to be one of U.S. News and World Report’s Top 50 undergraduate business schools in the
      country. For this ranking, it was the unusual number of options that Temple provides its RMI students – along
      with the school’s designation as a Center of Actuarial Excellence – that catapulted it to the #1 spot. With
      distinct specializations in Actuarial Science, Healthcare Management, and Risk Management & Insurance, this top
      undergraduate risk management program puts a premium on skill development and industry marketability – while also
      easily outshining its competition.</p>
    <p>Annual Net Price: $20,236</p>
    <p>Score: 100.0</p>
