    <h3 class="name text-center">2. St Johns University - Queens, NY</h3>
    <p class="description">Offered through St. John’s University’s Manhattan campus, the Peter J. Tobin College of
      Business provides one of the best insurance and risk management studies programs for globally minded students. In
      addition to the generally cosmopolitan vibe of New York City, RMI students at St. John’s enjoy internships with
      international insurance firms and a variety of study abroad opportunities, including trips to Rome and Paris. St.
      John’s also offers a Quantitative Risk and Insurance (QRI) track within the RMI program itself—an option that
      will help graduates become attractive candidates to global insurance and asset management firms.</p>
    <p>Annual Net Price: $27,390</p>
    <p>Score: 87.0</p>
  </div>
  </div>

</section>
